body_html:
The failure on pytorch-linux-trusty-py3.6-gcc5.4 seems unrelated to the macro change. It looks like ONNXBot updated ir.h to use std::sqrt and that's complaining, possibly because it's including math.h (which may not define names in std).

(This failure is happening for other PRs, too)
